title: Business Intelligence Analyst
description:
We are seeking a talented Business Intelligence Analyst to join our team.

Responsibilities:
- This position involves optimizing data collection procedures and ensuring data quality.
- You will transform raw data into meaningful business insights.
- In this role, you will design and build interactive dashboards and reports.
- You will work with business users to understand reporting needs and deliver solutions.

Requirements:
- High School Diploma in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field
- 3+ years of experience in business intelligence analyst or related field
- Proficiency in Google Cloud
- Proficiency in SPSS
- Proficiency in R
- Proficiency in Python
- Proficiency in ETL
- Proficiency in Tableau

Preferred Qualifications:
- Experience with Database Management
- Experience with Statistical Analysis
- Experience with Reporting

Benefits:
- Health, dental, and vision insurance
- Flexible work arrangements
- 401(k) matching
- Collaborative and innovative work environment

title: Data Analyst
description:
Our client is looking for an experienced Data Analyst to help drive business insights.

Responsibilities:
- You will work with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and provide data-driven solutions.
- In this role, you will analyze complex datasets to identify trends and insights.

- Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field
- 1+ years of experience in data analyst or related field
- Proficiency in R
- Proficiency in SQL
- Proficiency in Data Quality
- Proficiency in Business Intelligence
- Proficiency in Big Data
- Proficiency in Hadoop

Preferred Qualifications:
- Experience with Data Warehousing
- Experience with AWS
- Experience with Predictive Analytics

Benefits:
- Professional development opportunities
- 401(k) matching
- Flexible work arrangements
- Competitive salary and benefits package

We're hiring a Data Analyst to help us make data-driven decisions.

Responsibilities:
- In this role, you will analyze complex datasets to identify trends and insights.
- You will work with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and provide data-driven solutions.
- You will be responsible for creating dashboards and reports to communicate findings to stakeholders.
- This position involves cleaning and transforming data to ensure accuracy and reliability.

Requirements:
- Certification in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field
- 4+ years of experience in data analyst or related field
- Proficiency in Dashboard Development
- Proficiency in Power BI
- Proficiency in ETL
- Proficiency in Tableau
- Proficiency in Spark
- Proficiency in Data Visualization

Preferred Qualifications:
- Experience with Big Data
- Experience with Excel
- Experience with Data Modeling

Benefits:
- Flexible work arrangements
- Professional development opportunities
- Health, dental, and vision insurance
- Collaborative and innovative work environment
